The paper deals with video analysis, specifically event recognition and person tracking, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and attention mechanisms also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) in the form of event classification, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with a specific application domain, basketball, which could potentially fall under multimedia (cs.MM).
